  "summary": "Using $e^+e^-$ collision data corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 19,fb$^{-1}$ collected by the BESIII detector at center-of-mass energies ranging from 4.13 to 4.70,GeV, we report the first evidence for a new excited $Ω^{-}$ hyperon, the $Ω(2109)^{-}$, through the process $e^+ e^- \\to Ω(2109)^{-} \\barΩ^{+} +c.c.$ with a significance of 4.1 $σ$. The mass and width of $Ω(2109)^{-}$ are measured to be $2108.5 \\pm 5.2_{\\rm stat} \\pm 0.9_{\\rm syst}\\,{\\rm MeV}/c^{2}$ and $18.3 \\pm 16.4_{\\rm stat} \\pm 5.7_{\\rm syst}\\,{\\rm MeV}$, respectively. We also present evidence for a new production mechanism for the previously identified $Ω(2012)^-$ via the process $e^+ e^- \\to Ω(2012)^{-} \\barΩ^{+} +c.c.$ with a significance of 3.5 $σ$.",
  "submission_date": "2024-11-18",
